 Port Elizabeth - The Port Elizabeth office of the SA Weather Service on Friday said that the rains that fell overnight were mainly confined to the coastal belt and adjacent interior. "The Langkloof, our main catchment received between 13 mm at Joubertina and 40 mm at Kareedouw," said Garth Sampson, Client Liaison Officer Eastern Cape South African Weather Service. "The Kouga catchment received a mere 3 mm at Patensie. "Over the interior temperatures dropped as low as -2 C in places, such as Barkley East and Molteno." Sampson said that conditions are expected to clear gradually from the west later. Station Names 12 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 17.6 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 18.8 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 5.5 ARS Chetty 6.8 AWS Coega 2.0 AWSH Fettes Road 11.8 ARS Flower Reserve 8.0 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 9.4 ARS St Albans 5.2 AWS Uitenhage NIL MAN Woodridge 2.8 Catchment  AWS Joubertina 13.4 ARS Kareedouw * Man Kareedouw 41.0 Man Kouga Dam * AWS Patensie 2.8    Other Towns  AWS Addo NIL AWS Bisho/KWT 0.2 AWS Cape St Francis 9.0 AWS Cradock NIL AWS East London NIL AWS Fort Beaufort NIL AWS George 0.8 AWS Graaff Reinet NIL AWS Grahamstown 7.8 AWS Henry`s Flats NIL  Joubertina 13.4  Mossel Bay 1.4 AWS Mthatha NIL AWS Plettenberg bay 7.8 AWS Port Alfred 2.8 AWS Queenstown NIL  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  